{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Grpv9crFn1QTTWGaoPHGaz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files for what appears to be a recipe processing system. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. Save to `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.18.txt`\n2. Filename rules:\n   - Use SPACES (not hyphens/underscores)\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match content title (case-insensitive)\n\n3. Recipe mix: ~60% English (~6), ~40% Polish (~4)\n4. Categories: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n5. Mix of single-word and multi-word titles\n\n6. Pattern requirements:\n   - 5 files with MULTILANG (Polish + English variants, maybe another script)\n   - 3 files with COMPOUND (multiple recipes/variations in one title)\n   - 2 files with SIMPLE (basic OCR noise, stray numbers, page headers)\n\n7. File length: 15-60 lines (spillover = longer 40-60)\n\n8. Don't use these existing recipes (there's a long list provided)\n\nLet me plan 10 recipes:\n\nMULTILANG (5):\n1. Zupa Jarzynowa / Vegetable Garden Soup\n2. Pierogi Ziemniaczane z Krowiem / Potato and Cheese Pierogi\n3. Żelazo Mięsa / Beef Jelly\n4. Placki Owocowe / Fruit Pancakes\n5. Krem Serowy / Cheese Cream\n\nCOMPOUND (3):\n1. HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION\n2. WHOLE WHEAT BREAD WITH SEEDS : SOURDOUGH VARIATION\n3. CARAMELIZED ONION TART : VEGETARIAN VERSION\n\n\nSIMPLE (2):\n1. Tomato and Basil Risotto (with OCR noise)\n2. Polish Bigos (with OCR noise)\n\nNone of these appear in the exclusion list. Now I'll generate realistic OCR text with typical artifacts like character misrecognition (l→1, O→0), broken words at line breaks, page numbers, headers, extra spacing, and garbled sections. Each file will include ingredient lists with quantities and numbered instruction steps.\n\nPlanning to create: Zupa Jarzynowa / Vegetable Garden Soup (multilingual, 25-35 lines), Pierogi Ziemniaczane z Krowiem / Potato and Cheese Pierogi (multilingual, 30-40 lines), Żelazo Mięsa / Beef Jelly (multilingual, 20-30 lines), Placki Owocowe / Fruit Pancakes (multilingual, 25-35 lines), Krem Serowy / Cheese Cream (multilingual, 20-30 lines), Herb Baked Salmon + Dill Sauce Variation (compound, 40-50 lines), Whole Wheat Bread with Seeds : Sourdough Variation (compound, 45-55 lines), Caramelized Onion Tart : Vegetarian Version (compound, 35-45 lines), Tomato and Basil Risotto (simple with noise, 30-40 lines), and Bigos Myśliwski (simple with noise, 35-45 lines).\n\nFor the multilingual entries, I'll format them with the Polish title first, then English translation, followed by the recipe content. The compound recipes will include both variations in a single document. The OCR noise versions will have page numbers and intentional scanning artifacts mixed into the text to simulate authentic degraded document quality.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14515,"cache_read_input_tokens":65286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14515},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0106ce13-08d5-43a6-a448-719c55f91b7c","uuid":"bb461512-78e0-410b-b73c-539fee44ac9e"}
