{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01E5yE5b83ZkfFjEs46QABqT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013VeVE63hkz3R3TpCFfpwV9","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/CARAMELIZED ONION TART : VEGETARIAN VERSION.generated.18.txt","content":"CARAMELIZED ONION TART : VEGETARIAN VERSION\n\nCARAMELIZED ONION TART WITH GOAT CHEESE\n\nCrust:\n- 1.5 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1/2 cup cold butter, cubed\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1 egg yolk\n- 3-4 tbsp ice water\n\nFilling:\n- 1.5 kg onions, thinly sliced\n- 3 tbsp butter\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tbsp balsamic vinegar\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- 150g goat cheese, crumbled\n- 2 eggs\n- 1/2 cup heavy cream\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 1/4 tsp white pepper\n- Fresh thyme\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. Make crust: combine flour and salt. Cut in cold butter until breadcrumbs form.\n2. Mix egg yolk with ice water, add to flour mixture until dough forms.\n3. Press into 9-inch tart pan, prick base, chill 30 minutes.\n4. Preheat oven to 375°F. Bake crust 10 minutes until partially cooked.\n5. For filling: melt butter with oil in large skillet over low heat.\n6. Add onions and cook slowly 40-50 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n7. Onions should be golden and very soft, add balsamic and sugar at end.\n8. Spread caramelized onions in partially baked crust.\n9. Scatter goat cheese over onions.\n10. Whisk eggs with cream, salt, and pepper.\n11. Pour custard mixture over onions and cheese.\n12. Bake 25-30 minutes until custard sets and top is golden.\n13. Sprinkle with fresh thyme before serving.\n\nServes 8 as appetizer, 4-6 as main course.\n\n---\n\nVEGETARIAN VARIATION (WITH MUSHROOMS & WALNUT)\n\nAdditions to filling:\n- 400g mixed mushrooms, sliced\n- 1/2 cup walnuts, toasted and roughly chopped\n- 2 tbsp soy sauce\n- 1 tbsp miso paste\n- 150g sharp cheddar cheese (instead of goat cheese)\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. Follow crust preparation as above.\n2. When caramelizing onions, add sliced mushrooms at halfway point.\n3. Continue cooking until mushrooms release liquid and evaporate.\n4. In final minute, add soy sauce and miso paste, stir well.\n5. Spread mixture in crust.\n6. Add toasted walnuts to custard mixture along with the cream and eggs.\n7. Scatter cheddar cheese over base.\n8. Pour walnut custard mixture over.\n9. Bake 25-30 minutes as original recipe.\n10. Add fresh sage or parsley garnish.\n\nThis variation is heartier and works well as vegetarian main course with side salad.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":812,"cache_read_input_tokens":84136,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":812},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0106ce13-08d5-43a6-a448-719c55f91b7c","uuid":"36fbab59-67f4-4599-b4f5-fc1d7fecf7d9"}
